The CUDAHY PACKING COMPANY, a Corporation, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. Carter H. HARRISON, Collector of Internal Revenue, Defendant-Appellee. No. 6585. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Feb. 21, 1939.

Before EVANS and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellant, cottnsel for appellee consenting thereto, it is ordered, adjudged and decreed by this court that this appeal, 18 F.Supp. 250, be, and the same is hereby, dismissed.
